President Donald J. Trump has declared a state of emergency in Louisiana due to the emergency conditions caused by Hurricane Sally. The declaration authorizes the Department of Homeland Security and FEMA to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to alleviate hardship and suffering. Public assistance, including direct federal assistance, will be provided for various parishes in Louisiana. John E. Long has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. For further information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.